An early morning fire outbreak on Wednesday has razed down some shops at the Apongbon under Bridge Market in Lagos.
Although details of the fire and its cause are still sketchy, it was gathered that it started at in the morning. As at the time of filing this report, the fire was still raging.
Some vehicles parked under the bridge were also gutted by the fire which has enveloped a large section of the bridge.
Officials of the Federal and Lagos State Fire Service are currently at the market trying to put out the fire.
